flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Continuous ingestion of PLC/ICS telemetry, MES execution status, and SAP/PLM change events indicating a deviation in throughput, quality, or equipment state.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers + STREAMS - Ingest shop-floor telemetry, MES status, SAP orders and PLM events into foundation]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS (Subject Areas) - Normalize and compute KPIs (OEE, throughput, downtime, changeover cost)]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Process Builder - Rules - Evaluate deviation rules and severity using deterministic rules]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder - Remote Functions - Compute optimized reschedule and maintenance coordination}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Process Builder - Transaction + Notification (Remote Functions for ERP/MES API) - Execute transactional writebacks and trigger maintenance/work orders; send operational alerts]
  N5 --> N6[UI: UI Screen (dashboard) - Surface updated schedule, root-cause summary and KPI impact to operations and engineering]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Faster resolution of downtime events, lower changeover and idle costs, improved on-time delivery and utilization, measurable reduction in COGS and improved EBITDA via fewer prolonged stoppages and optimized capacity alignment.]
  N4 -->|Deviation classified as low-severity ...| B1[Auto-apply schedule tweak and maintenance suggestion; record action and notify stakeholders.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Immediate mitigation with no human intervention; reduced downtime and minimal disruption.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Deviation high-severity or impacts mu...| B2[Create CWB Lifecycle work item and route to operations/engineering for approval; hold automatic writebacks until approval.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Human-in-the-loop review prevents risky autonomous changes; preserves safety and quality while ensuring governance.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Telemetry or data inputs fail quality...| B3[Trigger Process Builder Wait + Notification to Data Ops and pause automated actions; fallback to conservative scheduling rules.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Prevents erroneous schedule changes due to bad data; ensures corrective data remediation before automation resumes.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]